#: src/rust-2018/trait-system/dyn-trait-for-trait-objects.md:1
msgid "`dyn Trait` for trait objects"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/trait-system/dyn-trait-for-trait-objects.md:3
msgid ""
"![Minimum Rust version: 1.27](https://img.shields.io/badge/"
"Minimum%20Rust%20Version-1.27-brightgreen.svg)"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/trait-system/dyn-trait-for-trait-objects.md:5
msgid ""
"The `dyn Trait` feature is the new syntax for using trait objects. In short:"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/trait-system/dyn-trait-for-trait-objects.md:7
msgid "`Box<Trait>` becomes `Box<dyn Trait>`"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/trait-system/dyn-trait-for-trait-objects.md:8
msgid "`&Trait` and `&mut Trait` become `&dyn Trait` and `&mut dyn Trait`"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/trait-system/dyn-trait-for-trait-objects.md:10
msgid "And so on. In code:"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/trait-system/dyn-trait-for-trait-objects.md:16
msgid "// old\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/trait-system/dyn-trait-for-trait-objects.md:21
msgid "// new\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/trait-system/dyn-trait-for-trait-objects.md:28
msgid "That's it!"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/trait-system/dyn-trait-for-trait-objects.md:30
msgid "More details"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/trait-system/dyn-trait-for-trait-objects.md:32
msgid ""
"Using just the trait name for trait objects turned out to be a bad decision. "
"The current syntax is often ambiguous and confusing, even to veterans, and "
"favors a feature that is not more frequently used than its alternatives, is "
"sometimes slower, and often cannot be used at all when its alternatives can."
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/trait-system/dyn-trait-for-trait-objects.md:37
msgid ""
"Furthermore, with `impl Trait` arriving, \"`impl Trait` vs `dyn Trait`\" is "
"much more symmetric, and therefore a bit nicer, than \"`impl Trait` vs "
"`Trait`\". `impl Trait` is explained [here](rust-2018/trait-system/impl-"
"trait-for-returning-complex-types-with-ease.html)"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/trait-system/dyn-trait-for-trait-objects.md:41
msgid ""
"In the new edition, you should therefore prefer `dyn Trait` to just `Trait` "
"where you need a trait object."
msgstr ""
